  "name": "Stick-Fighting Counter",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/skills/blue_23.jpg",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<em>Using stick-fighting techniques both defensively and offensively, you can turn your parries into counterattacks.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Stick-Fighting Style, base attack bonus +4.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>While you are fighting defensively, as a free action you can select an opponent you have attacked on that turn and prepare yourself to counter one of its attacks. Once per round, when that opponent attempts a melee attack against you and the attack misses, the attacker provokes an attack of opportunity from you, provided that it is within your threatened area. You must use a club, quarterstaff, dan bong, sap, or tonfa to perform the attack of opportunity.",
